<DOCUMENT><publisher>Dow Jones &amp; Company Inc</publisher><fulltext>&lt;p&gt; International Business Machines Corp. agreed to acquire Vivisimo Inc., a privately held provider of enterprise search and navigation software, as it continues to expand its &lt;span class="hit"&gt;big data&lt;/span&gt; platform. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Financial terms weren't disclosed. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Pittsburgh-based Vivisimo has more than 140 customers--including Airbus, the U.S. Air Force and Social Security Administration--and its software helps organizations access and analyze massive amounts of information, also known as &lt;span class="hit"&gt;Big Data&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Earlier this month, IBM agreed to acquire Varicent Software Inc., a provider of software that analyzes compensation and sales performance. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; The deals come amid IBM's push to expand into complex, high-margin areas such as the business-analytics business, which mines unstructured data for insight. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; IBM said the Vivisimo deal will accelerate its &lt;span class="hit"&gt;big&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class="hit"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt; analytics initiatives by adding federated capabilities. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Write to Melodie Warner at &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Credit: By Melodie Warner &lt;/p&gt;</fulltext><pub_title>Wall Street Journal (Online)</pub_title><author>Warner, Melodie</author><abstract>International Business Machines Corp. agreed to acquire Vivisimo Inc., a privately held provider of enterprise search and navigation software, as it continues to expand its big data platform.</abstract><title>IBM to Buy Navigation Software Maker Vivisimo</title><document_url>http://search.proquest.com/docview/1009295230?accountid=14696</document_url><pub_date>Apr 25, 2012</pub_date><pq_doc_id>1009295230</pq_doc_id></DOCUMENT>